open NumberField

/--
**Finite-generation hypothesis** for the maximal unramified pro-`p`
Galois group of a number field.

Asserts that for every number field `F` and every prime `p`,
`Gal(F^{ur,p}/F)` is a topologically finitely generated profinite
pro-`p` group вҖ” that is, all five conjuncts of
`IsFinitelyGeneratedProPGroup` hold:

* the finite-topological-rank claim (the substantive content,
  cf. Koch *Galois Theory of p-Extensions*, Theorem 11.8 with `S = вҲ…`),
* compactness, Hausdorffness, total disconnectedness, and the
  `p`-group structure of every open-normal quotient (structural
  consequences of the construction of `MaxUnramifiedProPGaloisGroup`).
-/
def Hyp_FiniteTopologicalRank : Prop :=
  вҲҖ (F : Type) [Field F] [NumberField F] (p : в„•) [Fact p.Prime],
    IsFinitelyGeneratedProPGroup p (MaxUnramifiedProPGaloisGroup F p)

/--
**Five-term inflation-restriction relation bound.**

For every finitely generated pro-`p` group `G` with `HВІ_cts(G; рқ”Ҫ_p)`
finite-dimensional, and every closed normal subgroup `N вҠҙ G`,
`HВІ_cts(G/N; рқ”Ҫ_p)` is finite-dimensional and the relation rank of the
quotient satisfies
`r(G/N) вүӨ r(G) + h1NormalInvariantRank p G N`,
where `h1NormalInvariantRank p G N = dim_{рқ”Ҫ_p} HВ№_cts(N; рқ”Ҫ_p)^G`.

This is the direct consequence of the **five-term inflation-restriction
exact sequence** in continuous cohomology applied to `1 вҶ’ N вҶ’ G вҶ’ G/N вҶ’ 1`:
the segment
`HВ№(G/N) вҶ’ HВ№(G) вҶ’ HВ№(N)^G вҶ’ HВІ(G/N) вҶ’ HВІ(G)`
gives `dim HВІ(G/N) вүӨ dim HВІ(G) + dim HВ№(N)^G` (and the finite-
dimensionality of `HВІ(G/N)` from that of `HВІ(G)` and `HВ№(N)^G`, the
latter bounded by the next hypothesis `Hyp_NormallyGenH1InvariantBound`).

*References*: J.-P. Serre, *Cohomologie Galoisienne* (5e Г©d.),
Ch. I В§2.6 Proposition 17;  NeukirchвҖ“SchmidtвҖ“Wingberg, *Cohomology of
Number Fields* (2nd ed.), Proposition 1.6.7.
-/
def Hyp_FiveTermRelationBound : Prop :=
  вҲҖ (p : в„•) [Fact p.Prime] (G : Type)
    [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G] [IsTopologicalGroup G]
    [T2Space G] [CompactSpace G] [TotallyDisconnectedSpace G],
    IsFinitelyGeneratedProPGroup p G вҶ’
    H2Finite p G вҶ’
    вҲҖ (N : Subgroup G) [N.Normal] (_hClosed : IsClosed (N : Set G))
      (_hH1Fin : H1NormalInvariantFinite p G N),
      H2Finite p (G в§ё N) вҲ§
        relationRank p (G в§ё N) вүӨ relationRank p G + h1NormalInvariantRank p G N

/--
**BrumerвҖ“Koch / Burnside-basis bound on `dim HВ№_cts(N; рқ”Ҫ_p)^G` for
normally generated subgroups.**

For every pro-`p` group `G` and every closed normal subgroup `N вҠҙ G`
that is **topologically normally generated** by `k` elements
`g_1, вҖҰ, g_k` (i.e., `N` is the topological closure of the normal
closure of `{g_1, вҖҰ, g_k}`),
`h1NormalInvariantRank p G N вүӨ k`.

By BrumerвҖ“Koch, `dim_{рқ”Ҫ_p} HВ№_cts(N; рқ”Ҫ_p)^G` equals the minimal number
of `G`-conjugacy-orbit generators of `N` as a closed normal subgroup;
any explicit topological normal generating set of `N` is a witness, so
the bound by its cardinality is immediate.

*References*: H. Koch, *Galois Theory of p-Extensions*, Theorem 4.10
(Burnside basis for finitely generated pro-`p` groups); W. M. Sawin,
*An explicit lower bound for the unit distance problem* (arXiv
2605.20579), Lemma 11 (the one-relation version states the same bound
for `k = 1`).
-/
def Hyp_NormallyGenH1InvariantBound : Prop :=
  вҲҖ (p : в„•) [Fact p.Prime] (G : Type)
    [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G] [IsTopologicalGroup G],
    IsFinitelyGeneratedProPGroup p G вҶ’
    вҲҖ (k : в„•) (g : Fin k вҶ’ G),
      letI : (Subgroup.normalClosure (Set.range g)).topologicalClosure.Normal :=
        Subgroup.is_normal_topologicalClosure (Subgroup.normalClosure (Set.range g))
      H1NormalInvariantFinite p G
        ((Subgroup.normalClosure (Set.range g)).topologicalClosure) вҲ§
      h1NormalInvariantRank p G
        ((Subgroup.normalClosure (Set.range g)).topologicalClosure) вүӨ k

